cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically on the problem of removing text from natural images. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses a conditional generative adversarial network (cGAN) and end-to-end trainable FCN-ResNet-18 network, which are common techniques in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of multiscale regression loss and total variation loss, which are commonly used in the field of graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper mentions experiments conducted on synthetic images and datasets, which are common in the field of multimedia (cs.MM).
